</head>

<body>
<h1>Chaotic Evil</h1>
<p class="subtitle">From <a href="http://www.jonnydigital.com/">Jonathan's Reference Pages</a></p>
<hr><!-- ======================================================== -->

<p>
So we were playing <a title="D&D"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=D%26D&lastnode_id=170179">D&D</a> <a title="Chaotic
Neutral"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Chaotic%20Neutral&lastnode_id=170179">again</a> - a
popular <a title="geek"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=geek&lastnode_id=170179">geek</a> <a
title="pastime"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=pastime&lastnode_id=170179">pastime</a>, I'm told.
The only difference was that this time, I was <a title="Dungeon Master"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Dungeon%20Master&lastnode_id=170179">DM</a>ing - I
was the guy <a title="How to run a roleplaying game"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=How%20to%20run%20a%20roleplaying%20game&lastnode_id=170179">running 
the game</a>. Or at least, <a title="How to ruin a roleplaying game"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=How%20to%20ruin%20a%20roleplaying%20game&lastnode_id=170179">attempting 
to run the game</a>.
</p>

<p>
If you're not familiar with <a title="Dungeons and Dragons"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Dungeons%20and%20Dragons&lastnode_id=170179">Dungeons 
and Dragons</a>, the basic <a title="premise"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=premise&lastnode_id=170179">premise</a> is this.
Four <a title="burly"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=burly&lastnode_id=170179">burly</a> men with swords
and armor charge into an abandoned underground dungeon, kill the
monsters who live there, loot the bodies and charge out again. There's
more to it than that, of course - it's a simplification. It's also a <a
title="simplification"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=simplification&lastnode_id=170179">simplification</a>, 
although a fairly accurate one, that each member of the party has his
own area of expertise - typically one is a burly armored fighting man,
another a scrawny <a title="wizard"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=wizard&lastnode_id=170179">wizard</a> or <a
title="Simon the Sorceror"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Simon%20the%20Sorceror&lastnode_id=170179">sorceror</a>, 
the third a sneaky backstabbing lock-picking <a title="rogue"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=rogue&lastnode_id=170179">rogue</a> or <a
title="thief" href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=thief&lastnode_id=170179">thief</a>
and the fourth a pious <a title="lawful good"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=lawful%20good&lastnode_id=170179">lawful good</a>
<a title="cleric"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=cleric&lastnode_id=170179">cleric</a> with
all-important healing magic. Adventuring parties who forget this fourth
member tend to die a lot more quickly.
</p>

<p>
Now this <a title="cleric"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=cleric&lastnode_id=170179">cleric</a>, it's an
important role in the party for the reason I just mentioned. It's also
generally the only character <a title="archetype"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=archetype&lastnode_id=170179">archetype</a> left
for the player with the misfortune to show up late on the day we started
the new <a title="campaign"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=campaign&lastnode_id=170179">campaign</a>. Everyone
wants to play the greatsword-wielding maniac, the <a title="fireball"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=fireball&lastnode_id=170179">fireball</a>-slinging
mage or the <a title="ninja"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=ninja&lastnode_id=170179">ninja</a>-esque rogue,
but nobody wants to be what basically amounts to a walking <a
title="battery"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=battery&lastnode_id=170179">battery</a> of <i><a
title="cure light wounds"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=cure%20light%20wounds&lastnode_id=170179">cure
light wounds</a></i>.
</p>

<p>
<big>"New campaign? Alright, I'll be the cleric."</big>
</p>

<p>
<a title="Well fuck"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Well%20fuck&lastnode_id=170179">Well fuck</a>.
</p>

<p>
The players roll their <a title="ability scores"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=ability%20scores&lastnode_id=170179">ability
scores</a>. Our cleric rolls an 18, the highest possible value for an
ability score, for his <a title="Wisdom"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Wisdom&lastnode_id=170179">Wisdom</a> score. Remind
me not to let them roll their own ability scores. Forty minutes of
dice-rolling and pencil-scribbling later, I ask the cleric's player
which deity he worships. <a title="Pelor"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Pelor&lastnode_id=170179">Pelor</a>, the god of the
sun and all things good? <a title="Heironeous"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Heironeous&lastnode_id=170179">Heironeous</a>, god
of valor?
</p>

<p>
<big>"<a title="Umberlee"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Umberlee&lastnode_id=170179">Umberlee</a>".</big>
</p>

<p>
"I don't believe I know that deity. Who's Umberlee?"
</p>

<p>
<big>"<a title="Umberlee"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Umberlee&lastnode_id=170179">Umberlee</a>, goddess
of the sea. She's out of the <a title="Faerun"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Faerun&lastnode_id=170179">Faer&ucirc;n</a>
book."</big>
</p>

<p>
"Her <a title="alignment"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=alignment&lastnode_id=170179">alignment</a>?"
</p>

<p>
<big>"<a title="Chaotic Evil"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Chaotic%20Evil&lastnode_id=170179">Chaotic
Evil</a>."</big>
</p>

<p>
"..."
</p>

<p>
<big>"Oh, but I'll be <a title="Chaotic Neutral"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Chaotic%20Neutral&lastnode_id=170179">Chaotic
Neutral</a>, so it'll be okay."</big>
</p>

<p>
<a title="the cleric"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=the%20cleric&lastnode_id=170179">Connor</a> has a
way of putting things convincingly, so I let him play this character.
What's the worst that could happen? It's not like the character's
actually <a title="evil"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=evil&lastnode_id=170179">evil</a>.
</p>

<p>
<a title="I hate to say ''I told ya so'', even to myself"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=I%20hate%20to%20say%20%22I%20told%20ya%20so%22%2C%20even%20to%20myself&lastnode_id=170179">I 
hate to say "I told ya so", even to myself</a>. Several game sessions
pass.
</p>

<p>
"What do you mean, you ran out of <a title="cure"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=cure&lastnode_id=170179">cure</a> spells? Can't you
spontaneously convert to <a title="cure"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=cure&lastnode_id=170179">cure</a> spells?"
</p>

<p>
<big>"Nope. Since I'm a <a title="cleric"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=cleric&lastnode_id=170179">cleric</a> of an evil
deity I spontaneously convert to <a title="inflict"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=inflict&lastnode_id=170179">inflict</a> spells, not
<a title="cure"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=cure&lastnode_id=170179">cure</a>."</big>
</p>

<p>
Several game sessions pass.
</p>


<p>
<big>"I tear out the <a title="assassin"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=assassin&lastnode_id=170179">assassin</a>'s eye,
and scrawl a message into his back with my sharp <a title="trident"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=trident&lastnode_id=170179">trident</a>."</big>
</p>

<p>
Several game sessions pass.
</p>

<p>
"You find three old men in the storeroom, unconscious, <a title="bound
and gagged"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=bound%20and%20gagged&lastnode_id=170179">bound and
gagged</a>. One of them wears the <a title="holy symbol"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=holy%20symbol&lastnode_id=170179">holy symbol</a>
of the deity of this roadside shrine."
</p>

<p>
<big>"Pah, another trick. I leave, shut the door and summon a <a
title="Draegloth"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Draegloth&lastnode_id=170179">Fiendish Dark Elf</a>
into the room."</big>
</p>

<p>
and
</p>

<p>
<big>"Can I use content from the <a title="Book of Vile Darkness"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Book%20of%20Vile%20Darkness&lastnode_id=170179">Book 
of Vile Darkness</a>?"</big>
</p>

<p>
and
</p>

<p>
<big>"Great, I'm the last surviving party member. I become a <a
title="lich"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=lich&lastnode_id=170179">lich</a>."</big>
</p>

<p>
and then
</p>

<p>
<big>"I order my <a title="undead"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=undead&lastnode_id=170179">undead</a> <a
title="minion"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=minion&lastnode_id=170179">minion</a>s to turn
everyone in the castle into <a title="shadow"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=shadow&lastnode_id=170179">shadow</a>s."</big>
</p>

<p>
and finally
</p>

<p>
"...and what about the village of Talen's Forge, who rescued you from a
sinking ship all those years ago?"
</p>

<p>
<big>"I'll have them turned into <a title="zombies"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=zombies&lastnode_id=170179">zombies</a>."</big>
</p>

<p>
The world I spent several minutes creating lies in ruin, with half a
million innocent people massacred and turned into a cleric's <a
title="mindless undead slaves"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=mindless%20undead%20slaves&lastnode_id=170179">mindless 
undead slaves</a>.
</p>

<p>
"You see on your <a title="character sheet"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=character%20sheet&lastnode_id=170179">character
sheet</a> where it says <a title="Chaotic Neutral"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Chaotic%20Neutral&lastnode_id=170179">Chaotic
Neutral</a>? Rub that out and replace it with <a title="Chaotic Evil"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Chaotic%20Evil&lastnode_id=170179">Chaotic
Evil</a>."
</p>

<p>
<big>(<a title="smirk"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=smirk&lastnode_id=170179">smirk</a>)</big>
</p>


